Support class expressions: const C = class { ... } (#57)

Class expressions in variable declarations are now compiled as regular
class declarations using the variable name as the class name. The TS
type checker assigns an internal symbol name to anonymous class
expressions, so a classExprNameMap bridges that to the synthetic name
for struct resolution, constructor lookup, method dispatch, and
instanceof checks.

